# QueryMind — Implementation Plan

## Prompt & Dataset Analysis

### ✅ What You've Given Me (Summary)

| Aspect | Details |
|--------|---------|
| **Goal** | NL2SQL agent — user asks questions in English, system generates SQL, executes on real PostgreSQL, auto-corrects errors, logs everything |
| **Stack** | LangGraph + Groq (LLaMA 3.3 70B) + PostgreSQL 15 + pgvector + FastAPI + Flask |
| **Dataset** | Olist Brazilian E-Commerce — 9 CSV files already in `Dataset/` folder |
| **Agent** | 8-node LangGraph stateful graph with self-correction loop (max 3 retries) |
| **Backend** | FastAPI with async endpoints for query execution + analytics |
| **Frontend** | Flask with Jinja2 templates (Query Interface + Dashboard + Trace Replay) |
| **Testing** | pytest unit + integration + benchmark (20 queries) |
| **Docker** | docker-compose with 3 services (postgres, backend, frontend) |
| **4-Week Plan** | Provided via image — broken into Foundation → Core Logic → Interface → Production |

### 📊 Dataset Analysis

All **9 CSV files** are present in `d:\1 PROJECTS\QUERY-MIND\Dataset\`:

| File | Size | Table Name (PostgreSQL) |
|------|------|------------------------|
| `olist_customers_dataset.csv` | 8.6 MB | `olist_customers` |
| `olist_orders_dataset.csv` | 16.8 MB | `olist_orders` |
| `olist_order_items_dataset.csv` | 14.7 MB | `olist_order_items` |
| `olist_order_payments_dataset.csv` | 5.5 MB | `olist_order_payments` |
| `olist_order_reviews_dataset.csv` | 13.8 MB | `olist_order_reviews` |
| `olist_products_dataset.csv` | 2.3 MB | `olist_products` |
| `olist_sellers_dataset.csv` | 171 KB | `olist_sellers` |
| `olist_geolocation_dataset.csv` | 58.4 MB | `olist_geolocation` |
| `product_category_name_translation.csv` | 2.5 KB | `product_category_translation` |

**Key Relationships** (foreign keys to implement):
```
olist_orders.customer_id → olist_customers.customer_id
olist_order_items.order_id → olist_orders.order_id
olist_order_items.product_id → olist_products.product_id
olist_order_items.seller_id → olist_sellers.seller_id
olist_order_payments.order_id → olist_orders.order_id
olist_order_reviews.order_id → olist_orders.order_id
product_category_translation.product_category_name → olist_products.product_category_name
```

