## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Embedding Dimension Correction**: Your spec says `vector(1536)` for `schema_embeddings`, but `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` produces **384-dimensional** vectors, not 1536. (1536 is OpenAI's `text-embedding-ada-002` dimension.) I will use `vector(384)` instead. If you want 1536, we'd need to switch to a different embedding model.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Frontend Change — Flask instead of Streamlit**: Your spec header says "Streamlit" but the detailed frontend section describes Flask with Jinja templates, routes, and custom CSS. The 4-week image also mentions "Streamlit" in some places. **I will build the Flask-based frontend as described in the detailed spec**, since it's more production-grade and aligns with the detailed requirements. Please confirm.

> [!WARNING]
> **Geolocation table (58 MB, ~1M rows)**: This is the largest CSV. The `olist_geolocation` table has no unique primary key — it uses `geolocation_zip_code_prefix` + lat/lng which has duplicates. I'll handle this by adding a serial `id` column as primary key and creating indexes on `zip_code_prefix`.

> [!NOTE]
> **9th table**: The dataset includes `product_category_name_translation.csv` (Portuguese → English translations). This is useful for the NL2SQL agent to translate category names. I'll include it as `product_category_translation` table.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Frontend - Flask :5000"
        A["/ Query Interface"]
        B["/dashboard Observability"]
        C["/trace Trace Replay"]
    end

    subgraph "Backend - FastAPI :8000"
        D["POST /query"]
        E["GET /analytics/*"]
        F["POST /embeddings/rebuild"]
    end

    subgraph "LangGraph Agent Pipeline"
        G["schema_retriever"] --> H["sql_generator"]
        H --> I["sql_validator"]
        I -->|valid| J["sql_executor"]
        I -->|invalid| K["sql_corrector"]
        J -->|success| L["result_formatter"]
        J -->|error| K
        K -->|retry < 3| I
        K -->|retry >= 3| M["failure_handler"]
        L --> N["query_logger"]
        M --> N
        N --> O["END"]
    end

    subgraph "Data Layer"
        P[(PostgreSQL 15 + pgvector)]
        Q["8 Olist Tables"]
        R["query_logs"]
        S["schema_embeddings"]
    end

    A & B & C --> D & E
    D --> G
    G --> P
    J --> P
    N --> R
    G --> S
```

